                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> heh... twitching isn't a substitute...  try doing aow with a 6 cleric rotation and one or two of them aren't maxxed out on ft while the rest are...<br /><br />for smaller guilds you make do with what you have...<br /><br />more clerics would of course be preferable... but oh well...  twitching 10 times over the course of a 10 to 15 min fight isn't going to kill me and it isn't going to really hurt my dps that much...  and it sure as hell is going to be a significant factor in success... <br /><br />As far as feigning off aggro /shrug... too many high end mobs aoe to make it worthwile even hiding from the aoe...  much "simpler" to just practice good aggro management and maintain a level of damage which is going to keep you out of trouble...  the added benefit of a couple extra dots in "some" cases where you can reasonably feign off aggro isn't worth the effort or the risk of something going wrong...  besides... there's only so many spell slots... 1 slot fd, 1 slot qvox 1 slot mujaki... that leaves hmm....  5 slots left...  use 4 for dots (one of which is saryn's kiss)... 1 for *gasp* mindwrack or twitch...  you have whala... 3 dots to maintain with a fourth added in at times situationally...  no feigning needed...</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
